<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="176" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1268,2016]" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1448,1475]" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior and posterior margin and other parts of pronotum with scattered irregular dark spots (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 3a, c</figureCitation>
); anterolateral angle of pronotum distinctly projecting laterally (
<figureCitation box="[928,1010,1485,1511]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
); hemelytron with opaque ochraceous stripe laterally (
<figureCitation box="[326,432,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 3a, c</figureCitation>
); terga I–VI without punctures (
<figureCitation box="[788,869,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); middle part of lateral margin of dorsal pygophore opening narrowed anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[482,564,1557,1583]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
); vesica with an indistinct lateral membranous lobe (similar to 
<figureCitation box="[1259,1339,1557,1583]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1837,1862]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,166,1817]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Meschia quadrimaculata, male, genitalia. a, pygophore, dorsal view; b, phallus, dorsal view; c–d, parts of phallus, enlarged; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: ba, basal apparatus; bl, blade; bo, body; c, conjunctiva; cs, cuplike sclerite; dl, dorsal lobe of paramere; ds, ductus seminis; ej, ejaculatory reservoir; gp, gonoporal process; hp, helicoid process; id, indentation; lm, lateral magin of dorsal pygophore opening; mcp, median conical protuberance; ml, membranous lobe; ph, phallotheca; sg, secondary gonopore; w, wing; ve, vesica; vl, ventral lobe of paramere. Rectangle highlighted area indicates weakly sclerotized area of phallotheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673399/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
); middle part of paramere blade distinctly broader than basal part (
<figureCitation box="[793,929,1593,1620]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 4c, e, h</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="4" pageNumber="176" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1268,2016]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,153,1979]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="177" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1628,1655]" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[356,502,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Colouration:</emphasis>
Head ochraceous with dense brown punctures. Median area of head fuscous in darker specimens (
<figureCitation box="[362,444,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). Small conical protuberances anterior to juga pale (
<figureCitation box="[1029,1135,1665,1692]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 3e, f</figureCitation>
). Colour of antenna ochraceous to dark ochraceous, with segments III and IV slightly fuscous in some specimens (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1215,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1185,1215,1701,1727]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="176" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotal posterior margin with four or six, and anterior margin with two or three vague irregular dark spots or patches; other part of pronotum also scattered fuscous spots or patches or vague irregular dark bands in some darker specimens. Scutellum ochraceous to reddish ochraceous, with anterolateral angles, tubercles on base, one third of lateral margin and apex smooth, impunctuate and pale (
<figureCitation box="[560,667,1845,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="176">Fig. 3a, c</figureCitation>
). Corium ochraceous with dark markings on middle of apical margin and apical angle, unevenly scattered dark coloured punctures, so corium looks variegated. Corium subhyaline with opaque ochraceous stripe laterally. Membrane hyaline, slightly passing apex of abdomen. Ground colour of body beneath and legs pale ochraceous and with a vague fuscous band along distal part of sternum in one of the specimen examined. Punctures beneath of head darker or concolorous. Labium reaching to middle of sternite V (male) or posterior margin of sternite VII (female), with tip blackish brown. Pleura scattered with coarse dark ochraceous punctures. Metathoracic scent gland opening pale ochraceous, with tip blackish brown. Distal upper side of femora scattered dark spots. Claws dark brown. Basal part of sterna golden-orange. Outer laterotergites bicolored, with posterolateral areas darker (
<figureCitation box="[462,544,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">
<emphasis box="[199,525,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Structure and measurements</emphasis>
(male/female): Body (
<figureCitation box="[792,860,297,324]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
a–d) length including wings 4.14/4.71; maximum width 1.85/2.06.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">
Head: Length 0.66/0.67; width across eyes 1.34/1.47; interocular space 0.83/0.98; interocellar space 0.36/0.44; eyeocellar space 0.17/0.17; eye length 0.32/0.32; eye width 0.24/0.23. Base of head with many microtrichia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,184,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, head, ventral view; b, microtrichia on base of head, enlarged; c, antennal segments I–II; d, antennal segment III; e, antennal segment IV; f, tip of labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673405/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
a–b). Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[353,437,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[407,437,441,467]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="177" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
), length of segments: 0.31/0.30, 0.81/1.12, 0.65/0.76, 0.80/missing; antennal setae as in 
<figureCitation box="[151,217,476,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,184,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, head, ventral view; b, microtrichia on base of head, enlarged; c, antennal segments I–II; d, antennal segment III; e, antennal segment IV; f, tip of labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673405/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
c–e. Labrum length 0.12/0.12. Labium extending to middle of abdominal sternum V (male) or sternum VII (female), length of segments: 0.67/0.73, 0.97/1.07, 0.53/0.61, 0.73/0.81; sensilla on tip of labium as in 
<figureCitation box="[1303,1381,512,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1732,1757]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1698]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,184,1712]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, head, ventral view; b, microtrichia on base of head, enlarged; c, antennal segments I–II; d, antennal segment III; e, antennal segment IV; f, tip of labium." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673405/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">
Fig. 
<specimenCount box="[1354,1381,512,539]" pageId="5" pageNumber="177" type="generic">5f</specimenCount>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">
Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[418,547,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 3a, c, e</figureCitation>
), median length 0.94/1.02; width at posterior margin 1.74/1.99; width at anterior margin 1.01/1.15. Some specimens without obvious pale median longitudinal line. Anterolateral angle of pronotum with an acutely rounded extension laterally. Scutellum length 0.79/0.99, width 0.98/1.21. Length of hemelytra 2.71/3.17; length of corium 1.78/2.09; claval commissure 0.18/0.23. Clavus either only punctate in three longitudinal rows or with scattered punctures between inner two rows of punctures. Metathoracic scent gland as in 
<figureCitation box="[1324,1389,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1714,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,166,1694]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, metathoracic scent gland; b, suture between meso- and metapleura; c, sternites IV–V; d, anterior trichobothria on sternite V; e, tibial comb; f, hind claw complex. Arrows indicate spiracles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673407/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
a–b. Metathoracic spiracle spindle shaped, narrow, with simple filter processes (
<figureCitation box="[994,1075,729,756]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1714,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,166,1694]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, metathoracic scent gland; b, suture between meso- and metapleura; c, sternites IV–V; d, anterior trichobothria on sternite V; e, tibial comb; f, hind claw complex. Arrows indicate spiracles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673407/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 6b</figureCitation>
) (terminology used in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kment, P. &amp; Vilimova, J." pageId="5" pageNumber="177" pagination="1 - 59" refId="ref4757" refString="Kment, P. &amp; Vilimova, J. (2010) Thoracic scent efferent system of the Tessaratomidae sensu lato (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Pentatomoidea) with implication to the phylogeny of the family. Zootaxa, 2363 (1), 1 - 59. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2363.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Kment &amp; Vilímová 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kment, P. &amp; Stys, P. &amp; Vilimova, J." box="[333,540,765,791]" pageId="5" pageNumber="177" pagination="267 - 279" refId="ref4696" refString="Kment, P., Stys, P. &amp; Vilimova, J. (2012) Thoracic scent efferent system and exponium of Aphylidae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Pentatomoidea), its architecture and function. European Journal of Entomology, 109, 267 - 279. https: // doi. org / 10.14411 / eje. 2012.035" type="journal article" year="2012">
Kment 
<emphasis box="[416,473,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). Tibial comb and claw complex as in 
<figureCitation box="[970,1034,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1714,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,166,1694]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, metathoracic scent gland; b, suture between meso- and metapleura; c, sternites IV–V; d, anterior trichobothria on sternite V; e, tibial comb; f, hind claw complex. Arrows indicate spiracles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673407/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
e–f.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">
Abdomen: Abdomen connexiva exposed beyond middle of corium in both sexes. Terga without any punctures except distal part of tergum VII slightly punctate (
<figureCitation box="[712,795,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Outer laterotergites with fine punctures. Venter covered with sparse punctures, somewhat thickly punctate on lateral areas. Sterna III–VII increasingly greatly narrowed medially and moved forward for reception of ovipositor (
<figureCitation box="[798,883,909,936]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1875,1900]" captionTargetBox="[186,1436,166,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,166,1855]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Meschia zoui sp. nov. a, holotype, male, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, paratype, female, dorsal view; d, same, ventral view; e, holotype, head, dorsal view, f, same, ventral view; g, holotype, left antenna, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673401/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 3d</figureCitation>
). Median area of sterna III and IV broadly membranous in dissected specimen (
<figureCitation box="[506,590,945,972]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
). Spiracles and trichobothria as in 
<figureCitation box="[978,1043,945,971]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1714,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,166,1694]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, metathoracic scent gland; b, suture between meso- and metapleura; c, sternites IV–V; d, anterior trichobothria on sternite V; e, tibial comb; f, hind claw complex. Arrows indicate spiracles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673407/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
c–d.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,1979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">
Genitalia. Female: ovipositor and spermatheca as in 
<figureCitation box="[790,873,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
; spermathecal bulb moderately sclerotized, with a basal rim. Male: Dorsal pygophore opening with middle part of lateral margin narrowed anteriorly, with a pair of pointed protuberances; posterior margin of pygophore and cuplike sclerite not fused; median indentation in posterior margin shallow and narrowed towards caudal end (
<figureCitation box="[781,865,1089,1115]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
); tip of cuplike sclerite obtusely pointed (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1424,1089,1115]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
). Phallus (
<figureCitation box="[248,328,1125,1152]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
) generally similar to that in 
<emphasis box="[638,860,1125,1151]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">
<taxonomicName box="[638,857,1125,1151]" class="Insecta" family="Meschiidae" genus="Meschia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculata">M. quadrimaculata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Phallotheca and conjunctiva without any processes; vesica with a lateral membranous lobe; gonoporal process twisted three times (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1119,1161,1188]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
). Paramere with middle part of blade obviously broader than basal part (
<figureCitation box="[638,774,1197,1224]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4c, e, h</figureCitation>
); both dorsal and ventral lobes obtuse (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1281,1197,1224]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1852,1877]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,197,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,184,1833]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratypes. a–b, female, abdomen. a, abdominal dorsum, inner view; b, abodominal venter, inner view; c–h, male, genitalia. c, pygophore, dorsal view; d, phallus, dorsal view; e–h, left paramere, four different aspects. Abbreviations: III–VII, abdominal tergites; ba, basal apparatus; c, conjunctiva; gp, gonoporal process; id, indentation; ol II, ol III, outer laterotergites II &amp; III; ph, phallotheca; sp II–VII, spiracles on sterna II-VII; sm, spermatheca; ve, vesica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673403/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="177">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
e–h).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
